---
description: Playful editorial visual system constraints
globs:
  - "app/**/*"
  - "components/**/*"
---

Visual direction:
- Keep a calm editorial base, then add playful detail through motion and hierarchy.
- Avoid toy-like UI and avoid loud gradients unless explicitly requested.
- Reuse shared surface/chip/card patterns before creating new visual variants.

System rules:
- Use one coherent surface family (`surface-1/2/3` + shared border/shadow logic).
- Use one coherent chip/pill family for nav, tags, and filters.
- Keep radius consistent (panel > card > chip).
- Favor subtle hover motion (`translateY` small distances, soft shadow changes).
- Keep reading pages calmer than homepage/gallery pages.
- Keep homepage and fandom as highest-expression areas, but still in the same token system.

Typography and spacing:
- Preserve strong heading hierarchy and readable body line length.
- Prefer generous section spacing and avoid dense stacking.
- Use muted text for metadata; do not lower contrast too far.

Implementation preference:
- Prefer semantic CSS variables and shared utility classes over ad-hoc one-off values.
- Before adding a new style treatment, check if it can map to existing system classes.
